                    "updated": "2008-10-09T14:33:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24992",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=daledaledale",
                        "name": "daledaledale",
                        "displayName": "Dale Liszka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I also tried 76 with success.  I'm not an advocate of either, I just want Zend_Mail to send uncorrupted attachements out-of-the-box.\n\nThe weird thing is GMail manages to fix them somehow with 74, no other MTA does.  They do some freaky things behind the scenes there.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=daledaledale",
                        "name": "daledaledale",
                        "displayName": "Dale Liszka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-10T10:13:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-10T10:13:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25503",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=osolo",
                        "name": "osolo",
                        "displayName": "Oz Solomon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Note to Zend:\n\nYet another release of the framework was released without this fix.  I can't for the life of me figure out why such a trivial change wouldn't be merged into main.  As it stands, I have to manually patch all my servers which is annoying. \n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=osolo",
                        "name": "osolo",
                        "displayName": "Oz Solomon",
                        "active": true
